  "text": "Tissue separation assays. The tissue separation assays were performed largely as described in [CITATION_1] . One modification from the original protocol was the source of mesoderm. To ensure that the exact same region of the mesoderm would be dissected, independent of potential effects of exogenously expressed proteins on involution, we used, rather than involuted mesoderm, earlier preinvoluted mesoderm dissected from stage 10+ embryos [CITATION_2] . Non-involuted mesoderm already displays strong separation behavior in the assay [CITATION_3] . Statistical significance was determined using the Student's t test, each experiment (2-3 BCRs and 8-15 explants) being treated as the experimental unit.",
